Problem Link:-https://leetcode.com/contest/weekly-contest-289/problems/calculate-digit-sum-of-a-string/ [easy]

Divided the string into groups of k size and the size of the last group can be smaller thanÂ k. 
Then replaced a group with sum of the numbers in that group, repeated this process until s.length() < k.



solution:-
class Solution {
public:
    string digitSum(string s, int k) {
        int n=s.length();
        if(n<=k){
            return s;
        }
        while(n>k){
            int i=0;
            string ss="";
            int an=0;
            while(i<n){
                int c=k;
                int an=0;
                while(i<n and c--){
                    an+=s[i]-'0';
                    i++;
                }
                ss+=to_string(an);
            }
            s=ss;
            n=s.length();
        }
        return s;
    }
};
